{{Quote|The vua'sa was a vicious predator that at times multiplied so quickly, it left deserts behind it.|[[Nen Yim]]|<ref name="The New Jedi Order: The Final Prophecy">''[[The New Jedi Order: The Final Prophecy]]''</ref>}}
The '''vua'sa''' were dangerous predators from [[Yuuzhan'tar]], rare due to their high reproduction rate and tendency to depopulate their ecosystem. According to legend, the first [[warmaster]] created by [[Yun-Yuuzhan]] was not a [[Yuuzhan Vong]], but a weapons beast he named Vua'sa. A [[Warrior caste|Yuuzhan Vong warrior]] challenged the monstrous creature, slaying it and claiming its place as warmaster. [[Vua]] became a popular name among the warrior caste in honor of the first warmaster.

The vua'sa had been extinct since the loss of the Yuuzhan Vong's ancestral home planet, but its genetic code still existed in the great [[qahsa]] of the [[Shaper caste|shapers]] at the start of the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]]. After the loss of his foot in combat with [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]] on [[Duro/Legends|Duro]], Warmaster [[Tsavong Lah]] bade the shapers to create a vua'sa. In homage to the title of warmaster, Tsavong Lah engaged the vua'sa in single combat and bested the monster. From its corpse the shapers fashioned a foot with four obsidian-sharp talons. The four armored digits were an impressive symbol of the warmaster's power.

